      <p style="text-align:center;margin-left:0.01in;margin-right:0.04in;text-indent:-0.01in"><span style="font-weight:bold">Before: </span></p>
      <p style="text-align:center;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0.03in;text-indent:0in"><judge refersTo="#judge-the-honourable-mr-justice-peter-jackson" style="font-weight:bold;text-decoration-line:underline;text-decoration-style:solid">THE HONOURABLE MR JUSTICE PETER JACKSON</judge></p>
      <p style="text-align:center;margin-left:0.01in;margin-right:0.04in;text-indent:-0.01in"><docTitle style="font-weight:bold">IN THE MATTER OF MRS ANN CLARKE </docTitle></p>
      <p style="text-align:center;margin-left:1.96in;margin-right:1.99in;text-indent:-0.01in">- -  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - </p>
      <p class="Heading1" style="margin-left:0.5in">JUDGMENT </p>
      <p class="Heading2" style="margin-left:0.01in;margin-right:0.04in">(Approved for Publication) </p>
      <p style="text-align:center;margin-left:1.96in;margin-right:1.96in;text-indent:-0.01in">- - - - - - - - -  - - - -- - - - - - - - - - - - - - </p>
      <p style="text-align:left;margin-left:0.3in;margin-right:0in;text-indent:-0.14in"><span style="font-size:11pt">This judgment consists of 11 paragraphs.  Pursuant to CPR PD 39A para 6.1 no official shorthand note shall be taken and copies of this version as handed down may be treated as authentic. </span></p>
      <p style="text-align:center;margin-left:1.96in;margin-right:2in;text-indent:-0.01in">APPROVED FOR PUBLICATION </p>
